@node Main "Tri_Add - Documentation"

                             'Tri_Add' V1.1

                           by Charles-N. Jacob

  'Tri_Add' is a mathematical @{" puzzle " link play} where you add the numbers of
a pyramid-like board. Here's a simplified example of a typical game
(note that the actual game has 10 rows instead of the 4 rows
displayed here):

                             @{"2" link play}
                            @{"7" link play}@{"4" link play}
                           @{"5" link play}@{"8" link play}@{"1" link play}
                          @{"2" link play}@{"4" link play}@{"3" link play}@{"9" link play}

  You start from the top and you go down on each row. The lower
tile you choose must always be linked either at left or at right
from the upper choosen tile. As you descend in the pyramid, the
selected tiles form a 'path'.

  The game adds the total from the selected tiles and displays it
under the pyramid. When you get to the lowest row and your total
equals the total of the game, you win.

  Have fun!

