@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Tri_Add" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. 

                             How to play?

  To play, just click on a tile. If you start a game, click on the
uppermost tile in the pyramid and click on the lower tiles until
you reach the bottom of the board. The lower tile you choose must
always be linked either at left or at right from the upper choosen
tile. As you descend in the pyramid, the selected tiles form a
'path'.

  The game adds the total from the selected tiles and displays it
under the pyramid. For example it may be shown as: '8 of 41', where
'8' is the total you made and '41' is the total to get. When you
get to the lowest row and your total equals the total of the game,
you win. Then Tri_Add will display the number of moves you made to
complete the game.

  You can go back anytime, or even restart from the top of the
pyramid. If you restart from a tile lower than the top, the new
choosen tiles must always be linked with an upper selected one.
When you select a tile that is located higher than the last
choosen tiles, all the path previously created from that row will
be erased.

  You can restart the game anytime by clicking on the @{b}New Game@{ub}
button.

  Have fun!

  To quit the game, click on the game window's closebutton or by
pressing on the 'Esc' key.

